# AI Resume Tailoring Engine

## LaTeX Resume Output (Deterministic)

No AI decisions at this step ‚Äî generate LaTeX strictly from the tailored JSON.

**Fixed layout (in order):**
1. Header ‚Äî Name, Email, Phone, GitHub, LinkedIn
2. Skills ‚Äî one bullet per category (`Category: skill1, skill2, ...`)
3. Work Experience ‚Äî **always first**, no exceptions
4. Project Work ‚Äî always second
5. Certifications ‚Äî all on one line separated by `|` (if any selected)
6. Education ‚Äî always last

> `section_order` is hardcoded to `["work_experience", "projects"]` in the LaTeX generator. Any AI output suggesting a different order is ignored.

**Rendering rules:**
- Work Experience entries: `Company (bold) + location` ‚Üí `italic title + date` ‚Üí bullet points
- Project Work entries: `bold title + date` ‚Üí `italic role (if any)` ‚Üí bullet points
- Use the resume template preamble from `resume_template.tex` (includes font, margins, spacing)
- Escape all LaTeX special characters: `& % $ # _ { } ~ ^`

## Language Style ‚Äî Entry-Level Professional

All AI-generated bullet points, summaries, and cover letter content **must use entry-level professional language**:

- **Simple, clear sentences** ‚Äî avoid jargon, buzzwords, or overly corporate language
- **Honest and grounded** ‚Äî reflect real experience without inflating seniority (no "led teams of 50" when the candidate is a student)
- **Action-oriented but modest** ‚Äî use strong action verbs that fit a junior/early-career context: `Built`, `Developed`, `Assisted`, `Contributed`, `Implemented`, `Designed`, `Analyzed`, `Supported`, `Created`, `Tested`
- **Avoid senior-level verbs** ‚Äî do not use `Spearheaded`, `Orchestrated`, `Evangelized`, `Championed`, `Drove strategic vision`, or similar executive-level language
- **Quantify where honest** ‚Äî include real numbers and outcomes only when they are factually grounded in the candidate data
- **Cover letter tone** ‚Äî warm, professional, and eager-to-learn; not boastful or over-polished

## Bullet Point Conciseness ‚Äî Mandatory

Every AI-generated resume bullet point **must be concise and punchy**:

- **One line only** ‚Äî 10 to 18 words maximum per bullet
- **Cut all filler** ‚Äî remove "in order to", "was responsible for", "helped to", "worked on", "assisted with"
- **Lead with the verb** ‚Äî action verb first, result or impact immediately after
- **One idea per bullet** ‚Äî no semicolons, no multi-clause sentences, no run-ons
- **Format**: `[Action verb] + [what you did] + [result/metric if available]`
- ‚úÖ Good: `Built a REST API that reduced data load time by 40%`
- ‚ùå Bad: `Was responsible for helping to build and maintain a REST API that was used to handle data requests and in order to improve performance`
